{{Basketball Champions League Awards}} {{main|Basketball Champions League Awards}} The '''Basketball Champions League MVP''', or Basketball Champions League MVP of the Season, is the annual [[Basketball Champions League awards|award]] bestowed to the player that is deemed to be the "[[MVP|Most Valuable Player]]" during the full season of the [[Basketball Champions League|Basketball Champions League (BCL)]]. The Basketball Champions League is the [[European professional club basketball system|third-tier level European-wide]] men's professional club [[basketball]] league in Europe. The award is given by [[FIBA]]. The award has existed since the Basketball Champions's League inaugural season [[Basketball Champions League 2016–17|2016–17 season]].
==Voting criteria== The Basketball Champions League MVP is chosen by a vote of the fans online, a vote of media journalists and representatives, and a vote of all of the [[head coach|head]] [[basketball coach|coaches]] of all of the teams in each season of the league. The fans, the media, and the league's head coaches each get 1/3 of the vote distribution.
