{{Infobox cycling race | name = Cauberg Cyclo-cross | current_event = | image = | image_caption = | date = October | region = [[Valkenburg (city)|Valkenburg]], Netherlands | english = | localnames = | nickname = | discipline = Cyclo-cross | competition = UCI World Cup | type = | organiser = | director = | first = {{start date|2011}} | number = 7 (as of 2016) | final = | firstwinner = {{flagathlete|[[Bart Wellens]]|BEL}} | mostwins = {{flagathlete|[[Lars van der Haar]]|NED}} ''(3 wins)'' | mostrecent = {{flagathlete|[[Mathieu van der Poel]]|NED}} }} The '''Cauberg Cyclo-cross''' is a [[cyclo-cross]] race held in [[Valkenburg (city)|Valkenburg]], [[Netherlands]]. This race is up and around the famous [[Cauberg]], which is the final of the [[Amstel Gold Race]]. Since the 2013-2014 season it became a part of the [[UCI Cyclo-cross World Cup]]. In October 2017 there was no edition held, because the [[2018 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|Cyclo-cross World Championships]] is on the same parcours in February 2018.
