{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Damil Dankerlui | image = | image_size = | caption = | fullname = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1996|8|24}} | birth_place = [[Almere Haven]], [[Netherlands]]<ref name=sw/> | height = 1.72 m | currentclub = [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]] | clubnumber = 15 | position = [[Full back (association football)|Left back]] | youthyears1 = 2001–2005 | youthclubs1 = SV Almere | youthyears2 = 2005–2010 | youthclubs2 = [[Almere City FC|FC Omniworld]] | youthyears3 = 2010–2012 | youthclubs3 = [[Almere City FC|Almere City]] | youthyears4 = 2012–2015 | youthclubs4 = [[Ajax Youth Academy|Ajax]] | years1 = 2013–2018 | clubs1 = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] | caps1 = 0 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2013–2018 | clubs2 = [[Jong Ajax]] | caps2 = 71 | goals2 = 2 | years3 = 2018– | clubs3 = [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]] | caps3 = 7 | goals3 = 0 | club-update = 25 May 2017 }}
'''Damil Dankerlui''' (born 24 August 1996) is a Dutch [[association football|footballer]] of [[Aruba]]n descent, who plays for [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]] as a [[Full back (association football)|left back]].
==Club career== ===Early career=== Born and raised in [[Almere Haven]] to parents from [[Aruba]], Dankerlui began his football career with local SV Almere before transferring to nearby [[Almere City FC|FC Omniworld]] in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|title= Talent van de Maand Damil Dankerlui|url=http://www.almerecity.nl/ac-1/talent-van-de-maand-damil-dankerlui|publisher=[[Almere City FC]]|accessdate=30 October 2014|date=6 January 2012}}</ref> In 2010 the club was then rebranded as Almere City FC, from where Dankerlui transferred to the youth ranks of partner club [[AFC Ajax]] at the age of 16 two years later.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dankerlui verrast met overstap naar Ajax|url=http://almerecity.nl/teams/jeugdopleiding/home-jeugdopleiding/dankerlui-verrast-met-overstap-naar-ajax|publisher=[[Almere City FC]]|accessdate=30 October 2014|date=16 May 2012}}</ref>
===Ajax=== While registered as part of the clubs' B1 selection (under-17 team), he made his professional debut in the Dutch [[Eerste Divisie]] on 22 October 2013, playing for the reserves team [[Jong Ajax]] as a 69th-minute substitute for [[Derwin Martina]], in a 5–1 away loss against [[VVV-Venlo]].<ref>{{cite web|title=VVV vs. Jong Ajax|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/10/21/netherlands/eerste-divisie/vvv-venlo/jong-ajax/1478774/|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=13 August 2014|date=22 October 2013}}</ref> The following season saw Dankerlui registered with the A1 selection (under-19 team), where he made his continental debut at youth level in the [[UEFA Youth League]] on 21 October 2014, in a 2–2 draw against [[FC Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Damil Dankerlui - UEFA Profile|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefayouthleague/season=2015/clubs/player=250064842/index.html|publisher=[[UEFA]].com|accessdate=22 October 2014|date=16 May 2012}}</ref> Despite appearing on the bench for the first team of Ajax, he was never substituted on, plying his trade for the reserves team before leaving the club in January 2018.
===Willem II=== On January 9, 2018 it was announced that Dankerlui had transferred to [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]], signing a 2-year deal with the [[Eredivisie]] club from Tilburg.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dankerlui sluit per direct aan bij Willem II|url=https://www.bd.nl/sport/dankerlui-sluit-per-direct-aan-bij-willem-ii~a5a94b8f/|publisher=Brabantse Dagblad|accessdate=9 January 2018|date=9 January 2018}}</ref>
