{{About|the Andorran football club|the Scottish club|Rangers F.C.}} {{Infobox football club | clubname = Rànger's | image = [[Image:FC Rànger's.png|logo]]| fullname = Fútbol Club Rànger's | nickname = ''Rànger's''| founded = {{Start date and age|1981}} | ground = [[Primera_Divisió#Stadiums|Andorra Football Federation stadiums]]| capacity = | chairman = Rafael Amat Escobar| manager = | league = [[Segona Divisió]] | season = [[2017–18 Segona Divisió|2017–18]] | position = [[Segona Divisió]], 8th | pattern_la1=_blueshoulders|pattern_b1=_blueshoulders|pattern_ra1=_blueshoulders|pattern_sh1=| leftarm1=ffff00|body1=ffff00|rightarm1=ffff00|shorts1=0000ff|socks1=ffff00| pattern_la2=_yellowshoulders|pattern_b2=_yellowshoulders|pattern_ra2=_yellowshoulders|pattern_sh2=| leftarm2=0000ff|body2=0000ff|rightarm2=0000ff|shorts2=ffff00|socks2=0000ff| }}
'''FC Rànger's''' is an [[Andorra]]n [[Association football|football]] club based in [[Andorra la Vella]]. The team currently plays in [[Segona Divisió]].
== History == The club was founded in 1981, but they only started playing in Andorran leagues in 1999. After two years in the [[Segona Divisió|Andorran Second Division]], they played for the first time in the [[Primera Divisió|Campionat de Lliga]] in the 2001–02 season. After the promotion, FC Rànger's started a growing career, and after finishing second in 2005, they won the league title the two subsequent years, 2006 and 2007.{{citation needed|date=July 2012}}
FC Rànger's made their first time appearance in European competitions, playing the [[UEFA Intertoto Cup]] in the summer of 2005, being eliminated by [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]] by 6–1 in aggregate. The home match ended with a 1–1 draw, scored by Norberto Urbani. After winning the Andorran championship, they qualified for the [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]], where they were eliminated in the First round by [[FK Sarajevo]]. FC Rànger's became the first Andorran team to compete in the [[UEFA Champions League]] by qualifying for the [[2007–08 UEFA Champions League|2007–08]] season. However, their stay was short-lived as they were eliminated in the first qualifying round after a 5–0 aggregate loss to [[FC Sheriff Tiraspol|Sheriff Tiraspol]] over two rounds played on 17 July and 25 July 2007.{{citation needed|date=July 2012}}
At the end of the [[2008-09 Primera Divisió|2008–09 season]] the team was relegated. After two seasons in [[Segona Divisió]] the team finished second in the 2010–11 season and was promoted (promotion-ineligible [[Lusitanos B]] finished champion). In the 2011–12 season FC Ranger's finished 8th in [[Primera Divisió]] being relegated again to [[Segona Divisió]] where it has remained since then.
*'''Sponsorship''': **Pizzeria Venècia (2004–2006) **Construccions Buiques (2006–present)
