The '''Gran Premio Nobili Rubinetterie''' is a single-day [[road bicycle race]] held annually in [[Arona (NO)|Arona]], [[Italy]]. Since 2005, the race has been organised as a [[1.1]] event on the [[UCI Europe Tour]]. In 2010 the GP was split in two challenges, ''Coppa Papà Carlo''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/13th-g-p-nobili-rubinetterie-coppa-papa-carlo-1-1/results|title=Brambilla powers to victory|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=19 June 2010|accessdate=16 July 2012}}</ref> and ''Coppa Città di Stresa'',<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/13th-gp-nobili-rubinetterie-coppa-citta-di-stresa-1-1/results|title=Gatto gallops to sprint victory|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=20 June 2010|accessdate=16 July 2012}}</ref> but reverted to a single race&nbsp;– on the route of the ''Coppa Città di Stresa''&nbsp;– in 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.acarona.it/wordpress/14-luglio-appuntamento-con-il-15-gp-nobili-rubinetterie/|language=Italian|work=Associazione Ciclistica Arona|publisher=[[WordPress]]|date=18 June 2012|accessdate=16 July 2012|title=14 Luglio: Appuntamento con il 15° G.P. Nobili Rubinetterie|trans-title=14 July: Meeting of the 15th GP Nobili Rubinetterie}}</ref>

