{{infobox country at games | NOC = LUX | NOCname = [[Luxembourgish Olympic and Sporting Committee]] | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1980 | flagcaption = Flag of the Olympic Movement | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.cosl.lu }}&nbsp;{{fr icon}} | location = [[Moscow]] | competitors = 3 | sports = 3 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Luxembourg]]''' competed at the '''[[1980 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Moscow]], [[Soviet Union|USSR]]. In partial support of the [[American-led boycott of the 1980 Summer Olympics]], Luxembourg competed under the Olympic Flag instead of its national flag.
==Results by event== ===[[Archery at the 1980 Summer Olympics|Archery]]=== After not competing in archery in 1976, Luxembourg returned to the sport in 1980 with one competitor.
'''Men's Individual Competition''': * [[Andre Braun]] - 2386 points (→ '''16th place''')
===[[Athletics at the 1980 Summer Olympics|Athletics]]=== '''Men's 20&nbsp;km Walk''' * [[Lucien Faber]] :* Final &mdash; did not finish (→ no ranking)
=== [[Shooting at the 1980 Summer Olympics|Shooting]]=== '''50 metre rifle three positions''' * [[Roland Jacoby]] - 34th place
'''50 metre rifle prone''' * [[Roland Jacoby]] - 11th place
