{{NBA Development League Awards}} The '''NBA Development League All-Star Game Most Valuable Player (MVP)''' is an annual [[NBA Development League]] (D-League) award given since the [[2006–07 NBA Development League season|2006–07 season]] to the player voted best of the annual [[NBA Development League All-Star Game|All-Star Game]]. The inaugural D-League All-Star Game was held in February 2007, and the inaugural All-Star Game MVP was [[Fort Worth Flyers]] forward [[Pops Mensah-Bonsu]] of the East team.<ref name=bonsu>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/allstar2007/dleague_mvp_070217.html|title=Mensah-Bonsu, East Team Come Out On Top|work=NBA.com|date=February 21, 2007|accessdate=April 16, 2016}}</ref> By [[basketball position|position]], [[guard (basketball)|guards]] have dominated the award with five winners, followed by [[forward (basketball)|forwards]] and [[center (basketball)|centers]] with three each.
